.TH "blkcg_add_delay" 9 "blkcg_add_delay" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
blkcg_add_delay \- add delay to this blkg
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" blkcg_add_delay
.BI "(struct blkcg_gq *blkg "  ","
.BI "u64 now "  ","
.BI "u64 delta "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "blkg" 12
blkg of interest
.IP "now" 12
the current time in nanoseconds
.IP "delta" 12
how many nanoseconds of delay to add
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Charge \fIdelta\fP to the blkg's current delay accumulation.  This is used to
throttle tasks if an IO controller thinks we need more throttling.
